{
  "abstract": "Citation: G V Ranga Rao, S Marimuttu, Suhas P Wani and V Rameshwar Rao. 2010. Insects pests of Jatropha curcas., L and their management. Information bulletin. Patancheru, A.P. 502 324, India: International Crops Research Institute for the Semi-Arid Tropics. 24 pages.\r\nJatropha (Jatropha curcas., L) is an important bio-fuel crop across the globe. In nature this plant is attacked by several insect species of which less than 10 are known to be important, causing considerable damage to different parts at different stages of the crop. This bulletin provides short descriptions about the biology, distribution, damage symptoms and feasible management strategies of key species.",
